<!--EZCODE AUTOLINK START--><a href="http://pub57.ezboard.com/fverataesbladefrm29">pub57.ezboard.com/fverataesbladefrm29</a><!--EZCODE AUTOLINK END--> <br>
<br>
Many people go through their first levels in single group and solo encounters. For this reason many people once they get to raid level don't understand many of the important intricacies of being a member of a raid party.<br>
<br>
Lets start off with the easiest lesson.<br>
<br>
What makes a raid successful?<br>
<br>
Raids will vary depending on your goal. Are you seeking one target? Does it have multiple adds (monsters that will assist)? Does it AoE (area of Effect damage, spells, etc)?<br>
<br>
The easiest way to sum up success on a raid is if you achieved your objective (Boss MOB dead, obtained item, etc) and the raid party didn't get wiped out.<br>
<br>
So how do I help avoid a wipeout?<br>
<br>
Easy we just need to cover a few lessons<br>
<br>
Lesson 1....Main Assist<br>
<br>
Each raid will have a MA or Main Assist. This is the person who will keep the MOBs attention (aggro) so he/she takes all the damage so the raid party can maximize their healing mana pool with Complete heals on one person.<br>
<br>
Every person should assist the MA.<br>
<br>
Usually there will be a second assist named(SA) this person will take over as MA should the MA die as well as being responsible for tank mezzing unmezzable MOBs.<br>
<br>
Lesson 2.....Hotkeys<br>
<br>
Nothing will end a raid faster then breaking mezzes and not assisting. Hotkeys help you with this.<br>
<br>
If you don't know how to make a hotkey ASK.<br>
Some examples of hotkeys are:<br>
<br>
Main Assist--call the target &quot;I am attacking TARGET&quot;<br>
<br>
This will let the chanter know what MOBs to Mez<br>
<br>
Main Assist--call the assist &quot;Please assist me in Killing TARGET&quot;<br>
<br>
This will let the others know when to attack the MOB. We wait before attacking to let the MA generate sufficient aggro so when the others engage the MOB wont ping-pong. Assist call can take longer when a warrior is defensive due to his damage reduction. No matter how long it seems WAIT for the call. Personlly I prefer the MA to have his assist called in 2 consecutive lines so nobody can miss it.<br>
<br>
Melees/casters--many melees call their assist in raid channel, I'm not big on this as to me it just adds spam, there is no need to call your assist as if you better be assisting the MA's target. One thing that is ESSENTIAL is a hotkey that has a line that has /assist (MA's name). using the /assist name command is a guaranteed way to ensure you aren't breaking mezzes.<br>
<br>
Healers--call the heals &quot;Complete heal inc on TARGET in 10 seconds&quot; adding &quot;(Name) next&quot; is a good way to keep up on who’s next in a complete heal rotation.<br>
<br>
Pet classes--use the /assist name command but delay on sending your pet in. Sometimes an unmezzable MOB will come into the camp and the MA will call a new target. Make sure you have your pet back off ASAP or kill it if it wont respond. A dead pet is nothing next to a dead chanter and a dead raid party.<br>
<br>
Ok, so what's that Tank Mez thing you were talking about?<br>
<br>
Sometime an unmezzable MOB will present itself. On those occasions the chanter will call for a TANK MEZ(TM) on that target. The TM or SA will grab the MOBs attention and keep it occupied until the party kills the MA's MOB. Raid members should continue to assist the MA when a TM is called.<br>
<br>
OK, so I get the assist and hotkey thing, what's this enrage thing you’re talking about?<br>
<br>
Certain MOBs have special abilities that act as a proc. They are enrage, flurry, and rampage.<br>
<br>
Enrage-When a MOB enrages it ripostes every frontal attack. I've found enrages to last around 15 seconds +- a deviation. To counter this, the MA should turn off his auto attack. Other melee should move to the side or rear of the MOB as those attacks are safe. If movement is not an option, turn off auto attack. Missing an enrage message for any dual wielder usually results in a swift death. When you see the message, &quot;TARGET is no longer enraged&quot; it is safe to frontal attack.<br>
<br>
Flurry-When a MOB Flurries it gains a free round of attacks on the MA, whether that is a single or quad attack depends on the MOB. Spam healing from secondary healers is good to counter a Flurry.<br>
<br>
Rampage-Several Theories on Rampage exist but the most popular and supported by Logs and parser is this. When a MOB rampages it will get a free round of attacks on whomever is highest on it's rampage list(first person to engage the MOB who is in melee range). Rampages DO NOT hit the MA, but an alternate target. MA takes regular melee damage during this time. To counter a rampage MOB make sure a melee is the secondary person to engage a MOB. Often people are assigned as rampage tanks and given a cleric to watch their health. Important note-DO NOT rez anyone close to a rampage MOB as if that person was on the rampage list and is in melee range they will again be hit and More is being learned on Rampage and I will post any updates I get.<br>
<br>
Enrage, flurry, and rampage frequency can all be reduced with DEX debuffs.<br>
<br>
